 scenarios, is fraught with unintended consequences. <br></p><p><br></p><p>&gt; On 2016-02-01, at 23:28:36, Amir Michail via swift-evolution &lt;swift-evolution at swift.org&gt; wrote:<br>&gt; <br>&gt; <br>&gt;&gt; On Jan 31, 2016, at 6:10 PM, David Sweeris &lt;davesweeris at mac.com&gt; wrote:<br>&gt;&gt; <br>&gt;&gt; -1 because 64k isn&#39;t actually always enough for everyone.<br>&gt;&gt; <br>&gt; <br>&gt; I’ve been using the implementation of cyclomatic complexity in swiftlint and have not encountered any limitations that I couldn’t overcome by refactoring my code.<br>&gt; <br>&gt;&gt; - Dave Sweeris<br>&gt;&gt; <br>&gt;&gt;&gt; On Jan 31, 2016, at 08:45, Amir Michail via swift-evolution &lt;swift-evolution at swift.org&gt; wrote:<br>&gt;&gt;&gt; <br>&gt;&gt;&gt; I think that this one metric built into the language would have a huge impact on Swift development and for the better.<br>&gt;&gt;&gt; _______________________________________________<br>&gt;&gt;&gt; swift-evolution mailing list<br>&gt;&gt;&gt; swift-evolution at swift.org<br>&gt;&gt;&gt; https://lists.swift.org/mailman/listinfo/swift-evolution<br>&gt; <br>&gt; _______________________________________________<br>&gt; swift-evolution mailing list<br>&gt; swift-evolution at swift.org<br>&gt; https://lists.swift.org/mailman/listinfo/swift-evolution<br></p></div></li><li class="comment"><div class="avatar"><img src="https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/1f823d615b521ed15f1006b105c77900?s=50"></div><header><strong>Proposal: Require functions to have a cyclomatic complexity of &lt;= 10.</strong> from <string>David Sweeris</string> &lt;davesweeris at mac.com&gt;<p>February  1, 2016 at 11:00:00am</p></header><div class="content"><p>You’ve missed my point… (although, to be fair, it should’ve read “640k”)<br></p><p>Saying, as a language restriction, that you can’t have a cyclomatic complexity &gt; 10 is like saying that you can’t have more than x functions in a file, y lines of code in a function, or n properties in a struct. Why? What’s the point?<br></p><p>- Dave Sweeris<br></p><p>&gt; On Feb 1, 2016, at 08:28, Amir Michail &lt;a.michail at me.com&gt; wrote:<br>&gt; <br>&gt; <br>&gt;&gt; On Jan 31, 2016, at 6:10 PM, David Sweeris &lt;davesweeris at mac.com&gt; wrote:<br>&gt;&gt; <br>&gt;&gt; -1 because 64k isn&#39;t actually always enough for everyone.<br>&gt;&gt; <br>&gt; <br>&gt; I’ve been using the implementation of cyclomatic complexity in swiftlint and have not encountered any limitations that I couldn’t overcome by refactoring my code.<br>&gt; <br>&gt;&gt; - Dave Sweeris<br>&gt;&gt; <br>&gt;&gt;&gt; On Jan 31, 2016, at 08:45, Amir Michail via swift-evolution &lt;swift-evolution at swift.org&gt; wrote:<br>&gt;&gt;&gt; <br>&gt;&gt;&gt; I think that this one metric built into the language would have a huge impact on Swift development and for the better.<br>&gt;&gt;&gt; _______________________________________________<br>&gt;&gt;&gt; swift-evolution mailing list<br>&gt;&gt;&gt; swift-evolution at swift.org<br>&gt;&gt;&gt; https://lists.swift.org/mailman/listinfo/swift-evolution<br>&gt; <br></p><p>-------------- next part --------------<br>An HTML attachment was scrubbed...<br>URL: &lt;https://lists.swift.org/pipermail/swift-evolution/attachments/20160201/cfbca564/attachment.html&gt;<br></p></div></li></ul></li></ul></li></ul></li></ul></div>    </main>
